Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Calls Claims of Chinese Citizens Fighting in Ukraine "Completely False"

### English Text Summary:
Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Andrei Rudenko dismissed recent allegations regarding Chinese citizens participating in the fighting in Ukraine as "completely false." He expressed gratitude for China's balanced and precise stance on the resolution of the conflict in Ukraine. This statement followed Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky's claim that Ukrainian intelligence had identified 155 Chinese citizens fighting alongside Russian forces, which came after the capture of two Chinese nationals in Ukraine. The Chinese Foreign Ministry previously labeled these reports as "baseless."

